to do highlites, select the fill color, then change the color to a lighter color...then set the airbrush to 'screen' and change the opacity to like 6%...use a smaller brush (like a 36 or 27). make a new layer for both shadow and highlights.<br>
thats just one way...its prolly not the right way, but i dont' think there's a wrong way...just as long as it works. it works okay with metal...traum did a lil c&amp;c on my art here:<br>
